Wyo. (AP) -- Jurors saw photographs of Matthew Shepard's bloody face as prosecutors began presenting their case against Aaron McKinney, accused of beating the gay student to death in a drunken, drug-induced rage. They also saw pictures of the ponderosa pine fence where Shepard was left to die, his hands tied behind his back, and the pool of blood caused by more than a dozen blows as he fought his attackers. Shepard's mother, Judy, dabbed her eyes when prosecutors showed jurors the graphic photos while McKinney's father, William, bowed his head. McKinney barely glanced up. ``Matthew Shepard made a frail
